        h1
          | Consciousness:
          br
          |  essential components & infrastructure
        h4  Research project
      .row
        .col-xs-12.col-lg-8.col-lg-offset-2
          h3 Overview
          p
            | The aim of the project is to concieve a theory of consciousness and use it to design a digital infrastructure, upon which the creation of the suitable environment for the deployment of a consiousness will take place.
          p
            | "AI" is a bad term to use, which spreads confusion over the subject, therefore term 
            strong consciousness
            |  will be used. Intelligence is a certain  amount of interconnected data, consciousness is a property of functionaly divercified structure  with several obligatory features:
            ul
              li
                | Ability to operate conceptualy similar to neuron network: recieve, store and output data, experiencing constant change of low level structure  &#40; abstract layer defining structures directly involved in data manipulation &#41;
              li
                | Ability to operate on a permanent flow of data in real-time
              li
                | Presence of a number of constants and intervals defining certain properties of the system which can not be modified by it.
          p
            | The creation of the theory should rely heavily on two important sources: 
            ul
              li Psychoanalytic studies and research 
              li Neurobiology
            |           It is the combination of two that differentiates this project from the other ones in that area, focusing primarely on hardware principles of several processes said to be taking place in biological instances of an infrastructure capable of containining consiousness, here however we are looking at the system as whole and will work it down to recognize its parts and operations.
          p
            | When most of the projects have a goal of simulating activity of infrastructure, we will be going into describing it as a system starting with its 'software' components - consciousness, which sets requirements for the 'hardware' components and software architecture. Main ideas behind the researh: 
            ul
              li
                | Consciousness is a property of a physical structure, to be more precise - certain model of interaction between a number of data-processing structures which in total make up the infrastructure of consciousness
              li
                | Consciousness has strong relationship with what makes up the psychological activity taking place on the same infrastructure
              li
                | There is no consciousness as we know it without psychological activity, so to be able to create consciousness one has to understand and implement underlying psychological processes
              li
                | Creating consciousness is not so much about the hardware as it is about maping the main functions and relations which form consciousness and tracking down the laws and circumpstances which had led things go that way - coming up with genesis of consciousness is the crucial part of this project
          p
            | Instead of focusing on hardware itself and the way it operates like previous and ongoing AI research, this project is about grasping the system as a whole, and gradualy disecting it to get to essential parts to implement.
          h3  Participate
          ul
            li
              | Obligatory knowledge of psychoanalytic ideas based on minimum of all Freud&Jung works and additional readings in the similar fields
            li
              | Doctors are welcome, but it is not about experience, it is about the ability to analyze
            li
              | Additional areas of knowledge are very welcome: neurobiology, IT &#40;os architecture and operation knowledge&#41;
            li
              | There are no salaries or payments of other sorts, participation is voluntary; organization is of a non commercial nature
          p
            | Plan is to assembe a team for permanent operation consisting of not more than 5 specialists. Organisation will situate itself depending on geography of its partisipants.
